    <h2>Understanding Gluten-Free Dining</h2>

    <p>Before diving into the specifics of Chicken Salad Chick’s menu, it’s important to understand what it means for a food item to be gluten-free. Gluten-free foods are those that do not contain gluten, which is essential for individuals with celiac disease or gluten intolerance. Cross-contamination is also a significant concern, as even trace amounts of gluten can cause adverse reactions in sensitive individuals.</p>

    <p>When dining out, it’s crucial to communicate your dietary needs to the staff and inquire about the preparation methods to ensure that your meal is safe to consume. Many restaurants, including Chicken Salad Chick, have taken steps to accommodate gluten-free diets by offering specific menu items and providing information about potential allergens.</p>

